
00:00:01,461 --> 00:00:04,431
(thunder crashing,
wind whistling)

00:00:16,068 --> 00:00:18,103
What do you see
in the sky, Harper?

00:00:18,103 --> 00:00:19,905
Planets.

00:00:19,905 --> 00:00:21,940
The red one is Mars.

00:00:21,940 --> 00:00:25,611
The one with the rings around
is called Saturn.

00:00:25,611 --> 00:00:28,013
And the smallest one is Pluto.

00:00:28,013 --> 00:00:30,916
Oh, my little astronomer,
it's time to go to bed now.

00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:31,850
Okay.

00:01:00,679 --> 00:01:02,614
(thunder rumbles)

00:01:19,731 --> 00:01:21,667
(siren approaching)

00:01:26,538 --> 00:01:28,073
Okay, we have
a reported kidnapping.

00:01:28,073 --> 00:01:30,842
A five-year-old boy,
Harper Riordan.

00:01:30,842 --> 00:01:34,680
His nanny, Shelby Buress,
is also missing.

00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,381
What about the parents?

00:01:36,381 --> 00:01:37,849
Uh, parent. Single dad.

00:01:37,849 --> 00:01:39,618
A "T.C. Riordan."

00:01:39,618 --> 00:01:42,054
Said he was sleeping when
the nanny put the kid to bed.

00:01:42,054 --> 00:01:43,422
What time was that?

00:01:43,422 --> 00:01:44,856
Around 10:00.

00:01:44,856 --> 00:01:46,925
Woke up at 11:30,
went to check in on the boy.

00:01:46,925 --> 00:01:48,860
Did he make the 911 call?

00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:51,363
Yeah. 11:35.

00:01:51,363 --> 00:01:52,664
Half past midnight.

00:01:52,664 --> 00:01:54,933
Clock's got the
head start on us.

00:01:58,503 --> 00:01:59,838
Didn't you just say

00:01:59,838 --> 00:02:02,374
he was asleep at the
time of the abduction?

00:02:02,374 --> 00:02:04,109
Yeah.

00:02:04,109 --> 00:02:06,645
Is that how you
dress for bed?

00:02:06,645 --> 00:02:08,981
I dress a little less formally.

00:02:08,981 --> 00:02:11,083
Where's the boy's room?

00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:12,818
Upstairs.

00:02:25,797 --> 00:02:27,699
Okay, got some blood.

00:02:27,699 --> 00:02:30,035
Not a lot of it.
Definitely a struggle.

00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:36,708
Blood's tacky.

00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:38,010
Consistent with
the dad's timeline.

00:02:42,614 --> 00:02:46,685
I got a print... in blood.

00:02:46,685 --> 00:02:48,420
Definitely not
a five-year-old's.

00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:50,555
Our kidnapper, maybe?

00:02:54,593 --> 00:02:55,727
(camera clicks)

00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:02,868
Morgan, yeah,
I'm sending you a print.

00:03:02,868 --> 00:03:03,869
I want you to run it.

00:03:03,869 --> 00:03:05,370
I'm on it.

00:03:09,007 --> 00:03:11,076
(thunder rumbles)

00:03:13,912 --> 00:03:15,814
Look at that.

00:03:15,814 --> 00:03:17,082
FINLAY:
Blood on the ceiling.

00:03:17,082 --> 00:03:19,751
No, Saturn's missing.

00:03:23,388 --> 00:03:24,823
Metal particles.

00:03:24,823 --> 00:03:26,525
Could be transfer
from the kidnapper.

00:03:29,561 --> 00:03:30,996
Okay, I gotta get that
back to the lab.

00:03:30,996 --> 00:03:33,098
Why don't you have Hodges
come pick it up?

00:03:33,098 --> 00:03:35,500
I need you here.

00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:36,668
Hey, evidence coming through!

00:03:36,668 --> 00:03:37,803
Hold the door!
Hold the door!

00:03:45,444 --> 00:03:46,745
What part
of "Hold the door"

00:03:46,745 --> 00:03:48,380
don't you understand?

00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:49,881
I understood
all of it.

00:03:59,891 --> 00:04:02,928
(thunder crashing,
power whirring off)

00:04:02,928 --> 00:04:05,397
(alarm buzzing)

00:04:09,134 --> 00:04:11,369
Oh, brother.

00:04:11,369 --> 00:04:12,471
Oh, that is not good.

00:04:12,471 --> 00:04:13,772
BRASS:
It's not.

00:04:13,772 --> 00:04:16,508
A storm blew out
three generating stations.

00:04:16,508 --> 00:04:17,976
Power is out
in half the state.

00:04:17,976 --> 00:04:19,144
They say for how long?

00:04:19,144 --> 00:04:21,413
Could be a while.

00:04:21,413 --> 00:04:22,948
God, we already
lost enough time.

00:04:22,948 --> 00:04:24,416
You know the rule.

00:04:24,416 --> 00:04:25,484
If we don't find this kid

00:04:25,484 --> 00:04:26,818
in three hours, he's dead.

00:04:26,818 --> 00:04:28,120
If the lights don't come
back on,

00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,388
we'll find the kid in the dark.

00:04:38,029 --> 00:04:40,799
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:04:40,799 --> 00:04:43,802
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:04:43,802 --> 00:04:46,938
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:04:46,938 --> 00:04:49,107
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:04:49,107 --> 00:04:50,776
♪ I really wanna know ♪

00:04:50,776 --> 00:04:53,678
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:04:53,678 --> 00:04:55,147
♪ Oh-oh-oh ♪
♪ <i>Who... ♪</i>

00:04:55,147 --> 00:04:58,850
♪ Come on, tell me who are you,
you, you ♪

00:04:58,850 --> 00:05:01,753
♪ Are you! ♪

00:05:06,358 --> 00:05:08,827
RUSSELL: <i>Make sure the backup</i>
<i>generator's running.</i>

00:05:08,827 --> 00:05:10,595
And check the freezers.

00:05:10,595 --> 00:05:13,365
If we melt evidence,
bad guys walk.

00:05:13,365 --> 00:05:14,966
And lock down the guns
in Ballistics.

00:05:14,966 --> 00:05:17,569
Generator, freezer, guns.

00:05:17,569 --> 00:05:18,570
Copy that.

00:05:18,570 --> 00:05:19,571
All right.

00:05:19,571 --> 00:05:21,106
FYI, AFIS is out.

00:05:21,106 --> 00:05:22,707
So is CODIS and IBIS.

00:05:22,707 --> 00:05:24,743
Basically, all the "IS'es"
are down.

00:05:24,743 --> 00:05:26,611
We're just gonna have
to get used to it.

00:05:26,611 --> 00:05:27,846
Until the lights
come back on,

00:05:27,846 --> 00:05:29,915
we might as well
be back in grad school.

00:05:29,915 --> 00:05:31,850
Remember your basic
chemistry.

00:05:31,850 --> 00:05:33,718
Use your head, use your hands.

00:05:33,718 --> 00:05:36,555
And these cell phone batteries,
they're our only lifeline,

00:05:36,555 --> 00:05:37,956
so let's not waste 'em.

00:05:37,956 --> 00:05:40,592
We got a missing boy
and a nanny in the wind

00:05:40,592 --> 00:05:41,860
and we don't have much time.

00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:43,595
Head and hands. Got it.

00:05:43,595 --> 00:05:44,963
I got another call.

00:05:44,963 --> 00:05:46,598
Yeah, what?

00:05:46,598 --> 00:05:48,834
Yeah, heard the whole city's
blacked-out.

00:05:48,834 --> 00:05:50,602
What is that noise?

00:05:50,602 --> 00:05:51,970
It's the sound of...

00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:53,572
It's the sound of fear
and futility.

00:05:53,572 --> 00:05:56,541
Hey! You break that case,
you own it.

00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:58,076
This thing won't budge.

00:05:58,076 --> 00:06:00,478
It's not an escape hatch
if you can't escape.

00:06:00,478 --> 00:06:01,513
Where are you?

00:06:01,513 --> 00:06:03,915
We're trapped in elevator hell.

00:06:03,915 --> 00:06:05,784
Who's "we"?

00:06:05,784 --> 00:06:07,819
Me and-and... Henry.

00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,989
I was on my way to the lab

00:06:10,989 --> 00:06:12,991
to process that metal trace
that you and Finn found,

00:06:12,991 --> 00:06:14,726
and, uh, well, let's just say

00:06:14,726 --> 00:06:16,428
it's gonna to have to wait
until help arrives.

00:06:16,428 --> 00:06:18,730
I'll get Morgan
call Maintenance.

00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:21,900
Yeah, um, she might dial
the phone a little faster

00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,902
if you omit the part
about me being in here.

00:06:23,902 --> 00:06:25,370
Just a thought.

00:06:25,370 --> 00:06:27,772
What are you guys,
in high school?

00:06:29,507 --> 00:06:30,909
(camera shutter clicks)

00:06:30,909 --> 00:06:32,978
Hey.
Hey.

00:06:32,978 --> 00:06:35,547
So, we got blood splatter
on the ceiling,

00:06:35,547 --> 00:06:36,948
spatter on the sheets,

00:06:36,948 --> 00:06:40,418
and we've got this white
residue here.

00:06:40,418 --> 00:06:41,753
Go ahead and bindle that.

00:06:41,753 --> 00:06:45,023
Yeah. That's gonna be
the easy part.

00:06:45,023 --> 00:06:47,359
You know, if this turns out
to be important evidence,

00:06:47,359 --> 00:06:48,760
who knows how long
it's gonna take

00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,629
before we can process it
and get an answer.

00:06:50,629 --> 00:06:51,663
I know, I know, I know.

00:06:53,865 --> 00:06:55,500
Okay...

00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,836
no ladder outside the window,

00:06:57,836 --> 00:06:59,638
no tree that someone
could climb up.

00:06:59,638 --> 00:07:02,641
Dust along the ledges doesn't
seem to be disturbed,

00:07:02,641 --> 00:07:06,645
so our...
our kidnapper was already

00:07:06,645 --> 00:07:09,414
inside the house.

00:07:09,414 --> 00:07:12,050
FINLAY:
Hey, look at this void.

00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:14,719
Blood pattern is interrupted
right down this line.

00:07:16,521 --> 00:07:18,523
What do you think,
rug?
Yeah.

00:07:18,523 --> 00:07:20,458
Maybe somebody took the rug
out of here

00:07:20,458 --> 00:07:21,893
with somebody inside of it.

00:07:21,893 --> 00:07:23,929
And if this blood
is the boy's,

00:07:23,929 --> 00:07:26,131
that means he put up a fight.

00:07:26,131 --> 00:07:27,465
And lost.

00:07:30,035 --> 00:07:32,671
And that would explain
why there is no blood

00:07:32,671 --> 00:07:34,572
trailing out of the door
or in the hallway

00:07:34,572 --> 00:07:35,974
or down the stairs.

00:07:35,974 --> 00:07:38,076
Yeah. Wait, wait, wait,
let's back up.

00:07:38,076 --> 00:07:40,712
We don't know for sure that this
is the boy's blood, right?

00:07:40,712 --> 00:07:42,380
It could be the nanny's.

00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:44,115
We can't run the DNA
until the power's back on.

00:07:44,115 --> 00:07:45,650
So what do we do?

00:07:47,686 --> 00:07:49,354
We go old school.

00:07:49,354 --> 00:07:51,356
ABO typing. I like that.

00:07:51,356 --> 00:07:52,590
See, that's why you're here.

00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:55,093
I'll call Greg.

00:07:55,093 --> 00:07:56,094
SIDLE:
Hey, Nick?

00:07:56,094 --> 00:07:57,829
Yeah, I'm back here.

00:07:57,829 --> 00:08:01,766
Checked all points of entry--
no sign of a break-in.

00:08:01,766 --> 00:08:04,569
We could be looking
at an inside job.

00:08:04,569 --> 00:08:06,037
STOKES:
They look happy in this photo.

00:08:06,037 --> 00:08:07,939
I wonder what happened
to the wife.

00:08:11,109 --> 00:08:13,111
This is some serious
candle power.

00:08:13,111 --> 00:08:14,579
I mean,
it looks like T.C. Riordan

00:08:14,579 --> 00:08:15,847
is used to being unplugged.

00:08:19,117 --> 00:08:21,586
Got blood drops
on the table here.

00:08:24,055 --> 00:08:25,957
And a couple more
on the floor, see?

00:08:25,957 --> 00:08:27,125
SIDLE:
Mm-hmm.

00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:29,461
You know,
could be the same

00:08:29,461 --> 00:08:30,862
source as the blood upstairs.

00:08:30,862 --> 00:08:32,497
The boy.

00:08:32,497 --> 00:08:33,765
STOKES:
Yeah.

00:08:33,765 --> 00:08:35,633
Spines suggest directionality.

00:08:37,469 --> 00:08:39,137
Heading for the door outside.

00:08:39,137 --> 00:08:41,473
Let's see where the trail goes.

00:08:41,473 --> 00:08:45,377
How long has Shelby Buress been
your son's nanny, Mr. Riordan?

00:08:45,377 --> 00:08:46,644
From the minute
Harper was born.

00:08:46,644 --> 00:08:47,846
Shelby didn't do this.

00:08:47,846 --> 00:08:49,714
You sound pretty sure of that.

00:08:49,714 --> 00:08:50,715
I am.

00:08:50,715 --> 00:08:52,017
This is a very
big house.

00:08:52,017 --> 00:08:54,019
You must have a lot
of people working for you.

00:08:54,019 --> 00:08:56,888
Yes.
And I trust all of them.

00:08:56,888 --> 00:08:58,023
I'm gonna need a list.

00:08:59,724 --> 00:09:01,626
Do you and your wife share
custody of your son?

00:09:01,626 --> 00:09:06,731
My wife... my wife passed away
five years ago.

00:09:06,731 --> 00:09:07,966
I'm sorry.

00:09:07,966 --> 00:09:10,635
And you said
that you were asleep

00:09:10,635 --> 00:09:12,370
when Harper went
missing.

00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:13,605
I fell asleep in the den.

00:09:13,605 --> 00:09:16,508
In a tux?

00:09:16,508 --> 00:09:19,377
I was planning on
going out tonight.

00:09:19,377 --> 00:09:20,745
I changed my mind.

00:09:20,745 --> 00:09:22,580
So what woke you up?

00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:25,083
Nothing. Why?

00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:26,618
You didn't hear anything?

00:09:26,618 --> 00:09:29,521
No. I just...

00:09:29,521 --> 00:09:31,489
I just woke up.

00:09:31,489 --> 00:09:33,825
Well, we're gonna have
to take your fingerprints.

00:09:33,825 --> 00:09:35,493
It's just
a standard procedure.

00:09:35,493 --> 00:09:38,396
You know, so we can
exclude yours from
the kidnapper.

00:09:38,396 --> 00:09:39,964
And we'll need a blood sample.

00:09:39,964 --> 00:09:41,733
Fine.

00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:43,368
One last question.

00:09:43,368 --> 00:09:45,637
What is your son's blood type?

00:09:45,637 --> 00:09:48,506
I don't know.
No, it's fine.

00:09:48,506 --> 00:09:51,743
Uh, did he cut himself,
scrape himself recently?

00:09:51,743 --> 00:09:53,011
Maybe a bloody nose?

00:09:53,011 --> 00:09:56,881
He cut his chin
just the other day.

00:09:56,881 --> 00:09:58,750
The Band-Aid might
still be in the garbage can.

00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:01,920
And how did that happen,
the cut on the chin?

00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,621
He fell.

00:10:07,892 --> 00:10:08,893
BRODY:
<i>The Palermo?</i>

00:10:08,893 --> 00:10:10,462
Seriously?

00:10:10,462 --> 00:10:12,931
Okay, when do you think
engineers can be here?

00:10:12,931 --> 00:10:15,400
Oh, okay, thanks.

00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,634
For nothing.

00:10:16,634 --> 00:10:18,103
Henry and Hodges still
in the elevator?

00:10:18,103 --> 00:10:19,637
Hodges is in there?

00:10:19,637 --> 00:10:21,606
Just focus on Henry.
And this.

00:10:21,606 --> 00:10:22,874
What is it?

00:10:22,874 --> 00:10:24,142
Residue from the
missing boy's room.

00:10:24,142 --> 00:10:25,410
Oh, Without the Mass Spec,

00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:26,611
what am I supposed
to do with it?

00:10:26,611 --> 00:10:28,413
I don't know.
Be creative.

00:10:28,413 --> 00:10:30,515
Russell has me doing
ABO blood typing.
Want to help?

00:10:30,515 --> 00:10:33,918
Sure. Tonight,
everything old is new.

00:10:37,589 --> 00:10:39,524
♪ ♪

00:11:00,945 --> 00:11:03,615
♪ ♪

00:11:29,941 --> 00:11:32,010
♪ ♪

00:12:01,005 --> 00:12:02,707
I got clumping.

00:12:02,707 --> 00:12:04,709
You?
Yeah.

00:12:04,709 --> 00:12:06,044
Based on the Band-Aid exemplar,

00:12:06,044 --> 00:12:09,781
the boy's blood
type is O.

00:12:10,882 --> 00:12:12,784
You sure about that?

00:12:12,784 --> 00:12:15,019
Yeah.

00:12:15,019 --> 00:12:16,521
Why?

00:12:16,521 --> 00:12:19,524
FINLAY: What are you
doing out here?

00:12:19,524 --> 00:12:22,594
What, are you, uh,
communing with the stars?

00:12:22,594 --> 00:12:24,963
My cell phone's communing
with a charger.

00:12:24,963 --> 00:12:26,764
So what's your take
on T.C. Riordan?

00:12:26,764 --> 00:12:28,766
Why? What's yours?
Wouldn't be
the first time

00:12:28,766 --> 00:12:30,635
that a parent tried
to cover up abuse

00:12:30,635 --> 00:12:33,404
with a phony kidnapping report.

00:12:33,404 --> 00:12:36,441
Yeah, but let's not get
too far ahead of ourselves.

00:12:36,441 --> 00:12:38,576
Kidnapper hasn't contacted
Riordan with any demands.

00:12:38,576 --> 00:12:39,577
I know.

00:12:39,577 --> 00:12:41,546
I just...

00:12:41,546 --> 00:12:44,716
have a feeling this case is not
going to follow the rules.

00:12:49,387 --> 00:12:51,489
STOKES:
Blood trail's gone cold.

00:12:51,489 --> 00:12:52,890
No drops since the house.

00:12:52,890 --> 00:12:54,559
Rain probably
washed them away.

00:12:54,559 --> 00:12:55,493
(thunder rumbling)

00:12:59,030 --> 00:13:00,031
SIDLE:
Hey, Galileo.

00:13:00,031 --> 00:13:01,399
Yeah.

00:13:01,399 --> 00:13:03,101
No blood,
but check it out-- 11:00.

00:13:09,674 --> 00:13:11,042
STOKES:
Saturn.

00:13:11,042 --> 00:13:14,012
Planet from
the boy's room.

00:13:14,012 --> 00:13:15,747
(sighs heavily)

00:13:17,682 --> 00:13:19,851
Nick... and the missing carpet.

00:13:24,822 --> 00:13:25,957
(camera shutter clicks)

00:13:25,957 --> 00:13:28,860
It's awfully convenient.

00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:30,628
It's like we were
meant to find him.

00:13:33,431 --> 00:13:35,466
(sighs)

00:13:39,837 --> 00:13:40,872
STOKES:
Whoa.

00:13:41,973 --> 00:13:43,574
It's Harper's nanny.

00:13:46,577 --> 00:13:48,680
STOKES:
Got a knife right here.

00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:51,149
And something else.

00:13:58,356 --> 00:14:00,124
"We have Harper."

00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,635
Till I can see what I'm doing,

00:14:10,635 --> 00:14:12,837
I'm going to have to hold off
on the autopsy.

00:14:12,837 --> 00:14:15,907
But my initial exam says
the missing boy's nanny

00:14:15,907 --> 00:14:19,677
suffered two sharp force
injuries to the chest

00:14:19,677 --> 00:14:21,713
and...

00:14:21,713 --> 00:14:24,382
two more
to the upper back,

00:14:24,382 --> 00:14:26,484
all from
a double-edged blade.

00:14:26,484 --> 00:14:28,686
SIDLE: That and the width
of the wounds

00:14:28,686 --> 00:14:30,722
looks consistent
with the knife that we found.

00:14:30,722 --> 00:14:31,823
(electrical buzz)

00:14:31,823 --> 00:14:33,558
Things just keep getting better.

00:14:33,558 --> 00:14:35,893
Someone ask
for a light?

00:14:35,893 --> 00:14:37,495
Yeah, a light.

00:14:37,495 --> 00:14:39,130
That looks like
a moonshine still.

00:14:39,130 --> 00:14:41,566
Actually,
it's a slightly different kind

00:14:41,566 --> 00:14:43,501
of white lightning.

00:14:43,501 --> 00:14:44,836
Behold...

